Pre-Game Insights: Denmark is seen as favourites to win Sunday’s clash as well.
There are no fresh injury worries in the home team.
Dragan Stojkovic’s men, though, are not regarded as good travellers and we do not believe that they are capable of spoiling Denmark’s party at Parken Stadium.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Denmark will look to build on a 2-0 win over Switzerland when they take on Serbia in a highly-anticipated UEFA Nations League game.
The Danes kicked off their Nations League campaign in style.
Others: Patrick Dorgu is pushing for a rare start after scoring the opener against the Rossocrociati.
Lecce defender Patrick Dorgu is pushing for a rare start.
Stojkovic is unlikely to make changes to the team that faced the European champions in Belgrade.
